          "body": "The second divine speech (vv. 16-28) appoints a named commission to execute the distribution: Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun, and one nasi per tribe. The order is deliberate. Eleazar precedes Joshua because the lot is cast in the presence of the priest, and the Urim and Thummim govern the decision (cf. Numbers 27:21). Joshua follows because he is the civil and military leader charged with the conquest. The ten tribal princes follow as tribal representatives who ensure that the distribution honors each tribe's identity. Caleb son of Jephunneh heads the tribal list (v. 19), representing Judah — a detail not incidental. Caleb was the faithful spy (Numbers 14:24), the man who 'followed the LORD fully' when the rest of the nation refused, and who was specifically promised his inheritance (Deuteronomy 1:36; Joshua 14:13-14). His position at the head of the list is an act of covenant memory: faithfulness in the wilderness generation is honored in the appointment for the next generation."
